<subSubSection id="C363D3BEFFD9BF07D0D849A6FE86ECD2" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC68035FFD9BF07D0D849A6FE86ECD2" blockId="2.[151,1437,932,1569]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B90D5C27FFD9BF07D0D849A6FECDEBFA" bold="true" box="[151,273,932,957]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Eyespots sometimes present at prostomium. Lobes present on segments 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D41149A6FBB0EBFB" box="[1118,1132,932,956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D4E749A6FB6BEBFB" box="[1192,1207,932,956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
, sometimes also on segment 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D0B349CAFED1EBA7" box="[252,269,968,992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
; lobes of segment 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D1AE49CAFE33EBA7" box="[481,495,968,992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
beginning dorso- to ventro-laterally, extending across ventrum; lobes of segment 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D5C149CAFA40EBA7" box="[1422,1436,968,992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
inserted lateral to ventro-laterally. Three pairs of branching branchiae, on segments 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D40949EEFBAFEC43" box="[1094,1139,1004,1028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
. Glandular shields present from segments 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D1054E12FEA8EC6F" box="[330,372,1040,1064]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
through segments 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D21C4E0DFD40EC6F" box="[595,668,1039,1064]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12–16</number>
. Seventeen pairs of notopodia beginning from segment 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D5674E12FAE4EC6F" box="[1320,1336,1040,1064]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
, bearing narrowly-winged notochaetae. Neuropodia beginning from segment 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D3D54E36FC76EC0A" box="[922,938,1076,1101]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="5.0">5</number>
, bearing pectinate uncini throughout; uncini in double rows on segments 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D19B4E5AFDC7EC37" box="[468,539,1112,1136]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="15.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="11.0">11–20</number>
, rows with uncini in back-to-back to crest-to-crest arrangement. Genital papillae on segments 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D1664E7EFE8AECD2" box="[297,342,1148,1173]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C363D3BEFFD9BF07D0884E9DFBA7EE67" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC68035FFD9BF07D0884E9DFC85ED2B" blockId="2.[151,1437,932,1569]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B90D5C27FFD9BF07D0884E9DFEE7ECFF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1183,1208]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C79FBB6FFD9BF07D10B4EA3FE48ECFF" box="[324,404,1185,1208]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90D5C27FFD9BF07D10B4EA3FE48ECFF" box="[324,404,1185,1208]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Loimia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a confused taxonomic history, with several taxa mistakenly reported worldwide. The most useful morphological characters to identify the species within this genus are: (
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D4134EC6FBB4EC9B" box="[1116,1128,1220,1244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
) shape and position of the lobes on segments 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D1394EEAFE58ED47" box="[374,388,1256,1280]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D18D4EEAFE0EED47" box="[450,466,1256,1280]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
; (
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D1A34EEAFE27ED47" box="[492,507,1256,1280]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
) shape of ventral glandular shields and number of segments on which they are present; (
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D14F4F0EFED2ED63" box="[256,270,1292,1316]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
) number of uncinial teeth (from both anterior and posterior regions) as well as the general morphology of the uncini, including presence of processes and filaments (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D3174F2DFB55ED0F" author="Hutchings" box="[856,1161,1327,1352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1988) The Amphitritinae (Polychaeta: Terebellidae) from Australia. Records of the Australian Museum, 40, 1 - 60. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.40.1988.150" type="journal article" year="1988">Hutchings &amp; Glasby 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D4D84F2DFB0EED0F" author="Hutchings" box="[1175,1234,1327,1352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1995) Description of the widely reported terebellid polychaetes Loimia medusa (Savigny) and Amphitrite rubra (Risso). Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 92, 149 - 154." type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D4AF4F2DFA4BED0F" author="Hutchings" box="[1248,1431,1327,1352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Hutchings, P. A. (1997) The Terebellidae from the Wallabi Group, Houtman Abrolhos Islands, Western Australia. In: Wells, F. E. (Ed.), The Marine Flora and Fauna of the Houtman Abrolhos Islands, Western Australia. Western Australian Museum, Perth, pp. 459 - 501." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Hutchings 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D5134F32FA4BED0F" box="[1372,1431,1328,1352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D0D84F56FD8FED2A" author="Londono-Mesa" box="[151,595,1364,1389]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F. (2005) Terebellidae (Polychaeta) from the Mexican Caribbean with description of four new species. Zootaxa, 1057, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">
Londoño-Mesa and Carrera-Parra 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D2574F56FD8FED2A" box="[536,595,1364,1389]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D2114F56FC91ED2B" author="Londono-Mesa" box="[606,845,1364,1389]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. (2009) Terebellidae (Polychaeta: Terebellida) from the Grand Caribbean Region. Zootaxa, 2320, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="2009">
Londoño-Mesa 
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D35F4F56FC91ED2B" box="[784,845,1364,1388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC68035FFD9BF07D0884F7AFBA7EE67" blockId="2.[151,1437,932,1569]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
We agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D1C44F75FD36EDD7" author="Hutchings" box="[395,746,1399,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1988) The Amphitritinae (Polychaeta: Terebellidae) from Australia. Records of the Australian Museum, 40, 1 - 60. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.40.1988.150" type="journal article" year="1988">Hutchings and Glasby (1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D2B04F75FCE4EDD7" author="Hutchings" box="[767,824,1399,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1995) Description of the widely reported terebellid polychaetes Loimia medusa (Savigny) and Amphitrite rubra (Risso). Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 92, 149 - 154." type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8FDC4FFD9BF07D3C54F75FB4CEDD7" author="Londono-Mesa" box="[906,1168,1399,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. (2009) Terebellidae (Polychaeta: Terebellida) from the Grand Caribbean Region. Zootaxa, 2320, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="2009">
Londoño-Mesa (
<number id="3DB19212FFD9BF07D4024F7AFB54EDD7" box="[1101,1160,1400,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
regarding the critical importance of the morphology of anterior lobes and uncini, but we have herein recognized additional characters which are useful to distinguish between species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C79FBB6FFD9BF07D2914FC3FCF1ED9F" box="[734,813,1473,1496]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Loimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90D5C27FFD9BF07D2914FC3FCF1ED9F" box="[734,813,1473,1496]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Loimia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or at least for those occurring off the Brazilian coast. The presence of eyespots and their size, for example, should also be considered in species descriptions, as well as the number, arrangement and shape of mid-ventral glandular shields, as discussed below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
